1 Lalibela ##town %% churches carved from the living rock; built during the reign of Lalibela, namely during the 12th and 13th centuries; churches are also a significant engineering feat
2 Blue Nile Falls ##waterfall %% picturesque waterfall on the Blue Nile river; isolate the ecology of Lake Tana from the rest of the Nile; isolation has played a role in the evolution of the endemic fauna of the lake; no Nile crocodiles; hippos
3 Simien Mountains National Park ##national park %% highest point in Ethiopia; home to a number of endangered species; Ethiopian wolf; walia ibex (a wild goat found nowhere else in the world); More than 50 species of birds; arguably the finest place to trek in Ethiopia
4 Axum ##city %% obelisks; Northern Stelae Park; stelae are believed to mark graves; carved with architectural designs
5 Lake Tana ##lake %% source of the River Nile; largest lake in Ethiopia; formed by volcanic activity; a number of islands; ancient monasteries